About Us !!!
Wildwood Campground is located in central Florida just 2.5 miles from the beautiful and
historic
St. John's River
within the
Ocala National  Forest
. Our location is the
perfect place to enjoy outdoor sports and  recreation in a natural setting while
providing easy access to some of central  Florida's more famous
destinations.
Outdoor
Recreation activities include camping, RV park, boating, canoeing, fishing,
hunting, hiking, cycling, biking, trail riding, swimming, kayaking, horseback
riding, wildlife viewing, bird watching, photography, orienteering, off
road sites,  water skiing, snorkeling, tubing, & golf.
​
WILDWOOD CAMPGROUND
22113 State Road 40, Astor, Fl. 32102
Phone/Fax: 352-759-3538
Email:
[email protected]
A 55+ Community
Amanda Walton, Manager
We are 45 miles to I-75  and 35 miles to I-95 and many of the major attractions are within an easy
drive  time of one hour or less.  Just 25 minutes to Silver Springs and 45
minutes to  the Daytona Speedway.  40 minutes will place you on the
beach.
"
Our campground is a community of folks who come to stay or spend the Winter.
We have many activities throughout the year
.
